      <p class="section-label">Social Mission</p>
      <h2 class="section-title" style="margin-bottom:2rem;">Law in service<br>of the <em>community</em></h2>
      <p>The philosophy of Tesserae Bureau undoubtedly has a social function, oriented toward providing volunteer legal services related to social rights, human rights, and the protection of women.</p>
      <p>The firm's team has devoted considerable effort to providing legal assistance to vulnerable women and their families in labor and constitutional matters.</p>
      <p><em>"The vision of doing justice binds us indubitably to a humanist and moral sense, which seeks to combine the professional strengths of our team in favor of society's most fragile and exposed segment — women."</em></p>
      <p>The organization works in alliance with the <strong>Dolores Sopeña Foundation</strong>, a Spanish-origin foundation with presence throughout Latin America, including operations in Ecuador. The team provides unconditional support to this foundation's Quito office.</p>
      <p style="margin-top:1.5rem;"><em>"We are proud to be part of this new path!"</em></p>
      <a href="/en/contact/" class="btn-primary" style="margin-top:2rem; display:inline-block;">Request Pro Bono Assistance</a>
    </div>

